# ================================================
# GOLDEN STAR SCHOOL — Environment Variables
# Copy this to .env.local for local development
# Add to Vercel/Netlify dashboard for production
# ================================================

# Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here

# ⚠️  SECURITY WARNING — READ CAREFULLY ⚠️
# The service role key bypasses ALL Row Level Security policies.
# VITE_ prefix variables are embedded in the browser JavaScript bundle
# and are visible to anyone who opens DevTools.
#
# This variable is intentionally named WITHOUT the VITE_ prefix so
# Vite does NOT bundle it into the browser. It is accessed at runtime
# via import.meta.env but will be undefined in the browser — that is
# correct and expected behaviour for a browser-only deployment.
#
# For a purely browser-based SPA (no backend server), the service key
# MUST be kept in a Supabase Edge Function instead.
# See: supabase/README.md for the recommended Edge Function approach.
#
# If you are running the Express server (server/index.ts), add this
# as a server-only environment variable (no VITE_ prefix).
# It will NOT be visible in the browser bundle.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here
